data.title: Bloomington Qdoba
data.text: My daughter and niece just had to try the Qdoba here and my daughter said it was excellent. We also received excellent customer service, I would highly recommend this one

data.title: Solidly good food with generous portions
data.text: I often run to Qdoba to pick up lunch. Staff are always pleasant when I go there and I always enjoy my choice. Last month I had the vegetarian feature and was pleasantly surprised at how much I liked it. Portions are generous and so I am content to return and keep it on my "rotation" for quick lunches. I doubt it ever gets a grand award but it will keep a loyal fan base. I am in that group.

data.title: Nothing extraordinary
data.text: We came to try Mexican food, and instead we got mixed blotches of many different "things". The tortillas were warmed up, but not browned (it was sticky). The meat in all parts of the meal were nothing extraordinary. Certainly not a Mexican taqueria.

data.title: high quality Mexican
data.text: I went to Qdoba with my son and we both had quesadillas.  The quality is uniformly high.  There is no table service but the people behind the counter are helpful and friendly.

data.title: Great food and service
data.text: Never ate there but the servers helped us through the menu...very courteous staff...:-) Loved the choice of the pick two- having not had the food before this allows you to try out some options....:-)

data.title: Quick convenient made your way
data.text: This place is great for a quick lunch and also for a 'different' quick breakfast. They even let me bring my Starbucks in.  Okay, not gourmet, but burritos put together as you want!  Outside seating in a popular part of town  for warm days, nice windows for cold days.
